# Trivy ignore file — suppresses vulnerabilities fixed by pnpm.overrides in package.json.
#
# Each entry below has been addressed via a pnpm override that forces the
# affected package to a patched version.  The GHSA / CVE identifiers are listed
# so Trivy skips false positives produced when it inspects the overrides keys in
# pnpm-lock.yaml (e.g. "multer@<2.1.1") instead of the resolved package version.
#
# To re-evaluate, run: pnpm audit --audit-level=high

# minimatch — ReDoS in matchOne() (GHSA-7r86-cg39-jmmj)
# Fixed by: minimatch@3.1.4 / 5.1.8 / 9.0.7 / 10.2.3
GHSA-7r86-cg39-jmmj

# minimatch — nested *() extglob ReDoS (GHSA-23c5-xmqv-rm74)
# Fixed by: minimatch@3.1.4 / 5.1.8 / 9.0.7 / 10.2.3
GHSA-23c5-xmqv-rm74

# multer — DoS via incomplete multipart parse (GHSA-xf7r-hgr6-v32p)
# Fixed by: multer@2.1.1
GHSA-xf7r-hgr6-v32p

# multer — DoS via resource exhaustion (GHSA-v52c-386h-88mc)
# Fixed by: multer@2.1.1
GHSA-v52c-386h-88mc

# multer — DoS via tempfile cleanup failure (GHSA-5528-5vmv-3xc2)
# Fixed by: multer@2.1.1
GHSA-5528-5vmv-3xc2

# serialize-javascript — RCE via XSSI-style payload (GHSA-5c6j-r48x-rmvq)
